parties.raw_snippet:
This TRADEMARK LICENSE AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is effective as of the [·] day of [·], 2019 (“Effective Date”) between
Morgan Stanley Investment Management Inc. (“Licensor”), and Morgan Stanley Direct Lending Fund, a Delaware corporation (“Licensee”).
parties.reasoning: The clause explicitly names the two contracting entities and labels their roles (Licensor and Licensee). These are the primary parties to the Agreement.

contract_type.raw_snippet:
TRADEMARK LICENSE AGREEMENT

Section 1.1.License Grant. Subject to the terms and conditions herein, Licensor hereby grants to Licensee a non-exclusive, non-transferable, and (subject to Section 1.2 hereof) non-sublicensable license for the use of the Brand solely for the Permitted Activity.
contract_type.reasoning: The title identifies this as a trademark license and Section 1.1 describes the core economic substance: Licensor granting a license to use intellectual property (the Brand) to Licensee. This is an agreement primarily about licensing IP.

agreement_date.raw_snippet: This TRADEMARK LICENSE AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is effective as of the [·] day of [·], 2019 (“Effective Date”)
agreement_date.reasoning: The contract header contains the only date-related text; it uses placeholders ([·]) rather than a specific signing date. No explicit executed/signature date is provided elsewhere.

effective_date.raw_snippet: This TRADEMARK LICENSE AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is effective as of the [·] day of [·], 2019 (“Effective Date”)
effective_date.reasoning: The header defines the "Effective Date" as the [·] day of [·], 2019, but the actual day/month are placeholders, so no specific ISO date can be extracted.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: Section 4.1.Term. The term of this Agreement commences on the Effective Date and continues in perpetuity, unless termination occurs pursuant to Sections 4.2 through 4.4.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 4.1 explicitly states the term continues "in perpetuity," which is an explicit expression of indefinite/perpetual duration.

governing_law.raw_snippet: Section 9.4.Governing Law. THIS AGREEMENT SHALL BE GOVERNED BY, AND CONSTRUED AND INTERPRETED IN ACCORDANCE WITH, THE LAW OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK. EACH OF THE PARTIES IRREVOCABLY AND UNCONDITIONALLY SUBMITS TO THE EXCLUSIVE JURISDICTION OF THE STATE AND FEDERAL COURTS LOCATED IN NEW YORK CITY FOR THE PURPOSE OF ANY ACTION RELATING TO OR ARISING OUT OF THIS AGREEMENT.
governing_law.reasoning: Section 9.4 is the governing law clause and explicitly states the law to be applied: the law of the State of New York.

notice_period.reasoning: The contract contains termination provisions (including immediate termination on notice or termination for breach) but does not include any clause requiring advance notice to prevent an automatic renewal or any automatic renewal mechanism. Therefore there is no "notice period to prevent renewal" to extract.

renewal_term.reasoning: The Agreement states the term continues "in perpetuity" and contains termination provisions but does not provide any renewal or automatic renewal mechanism or renewal-term language.
